# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is inspired by Keep a Changelog and follows Semantic Versioning principles.

---

##[1.0.0] - 2026-06-23

###Added

*Rankings tab with 5 category views: Weekly Damages, Users, MUs, Countries, Alliances.
*Category selector pills switching between ranking views without page reload.
*4-panel grid layout per category, each panel displaying a ranked leaderboard (top 50 entries).
*Avatar support for Users, Military Units, and Alliances via media.warera.io avatar URLs.
*Country flag display from local assets/flags/ directory, keyed by ISO shortCode.
*Fallback initial-letter avatar when no image is available for an entity.
*Automatic entity resolution — fetches unknown user/MU/country/alliance profiles on demand.
*Dual-API redundancy — ranking.getRanking endpoint fetched from both gateway.warerastats.io and api2.warera.io.
*Rankings module directory: js/rankings/rankings.js.
*Dedicated rankings stylesheet: css/rankings.css with responsive grid breakpoints.
*ES Module architecture — full modularization of the codebase into independent module groups.
*Dedicated module directories: core, timeline, battles, market, jobs, ui, visuals, audio, intro.
*SFX system with 5 distinct sounds: click, read, copy, intro, api_saved.
*Settings modal with SFX volume slider and persistent localStorage configuration.
*Click-to-begin gate on the intro overlay ensuring reliable intro audio playback on first visit.
*Mobile responsive breakpoints at 1100px, 860px, 760px, and 420px.
*safe-area-inset support for notched and rounded-display devices.
*CSS organization — monolithic style.css split into variables, base, layout, components, visuals, intro, and responsive.

###Improved

*Codebase maintainability — monolithic script.js refactored into 30+ self-contained ES modules.
*CSS maintainability — single stylesheet split into 7 focused files with clear responsibilities.
*Audio reliability — intro.mp3 now plays in exact sync with the title reveal animation, respecting browser autoplay policy.
*Pulsating animation keyframes restored — 8 missing @keyframes (livePulse, liveRing, pulseBadge, modalIn, sweep, flashPop, toastIn, badgePulse) re-added to base.css after CSS split.
*Touch target sizing restored to compact original values (28–34px) — global 44px minimum removed from desktop.
*Date picker cleanliness — removed misaligned clear buttons from startTimeInput and endTimeInput.
*Removed all BGM code and associated controls from settings modal and module imports.

###Technical

*Modular architecture:
  -js/core/: api, constants, dom, resolver, state, storage, utils
  -js/timeline/: timeline, articles, events, filters
  -js/battles/: battles, battleDetail, companies
  -js/market/: market, economy, orders, valuable
  -js/jobs/: jobs, jobDetail, companies
  -js/ui/: toast, tabs, theme
  -js/visuals/: clock, oscilloscope, ecg
  -js/intro/: intro
  -js/audio/: audio
  -js/main.js as single entry point.
*CSS into: variables.css, base.css, layout.css, components.css, visuals.css, intro.css, responsive.css.
*AudioManager singleton with clone-on-play pattern for overlapping SFX and localStorage volume persistence.
*SFX click delegation — single document-level handler routing to playClick/playRead/playCopy based on target.closest() selectors.
*Removed console.log from tabs.js, 8 unused imports across 6 files, dead getItemCount function, 5 empty stub export files.
*Cancelled requestAnimationFrame loop in intro.js closeOverlay to free retained canvas context memory.
*Performance: will-change on animated/hover elements, content-visibility on inactive tab panels, passive resize listeners.

###UX

*Intro audio now reliably plays on first visit — click-to-begin prompt ensures user gesture before animation and audio start.
*Auditory feedback across all clickable elements with context-sensitive sounds for read and copy actions.
*Settings accessible via gear icon in top bar with instant SFX volume adjustment.
*Cleaner mobile experience with proper breakpoints and safe-area support.


##[0.4.4-beta] - 2026-06-22

###Added

*News Desk Information & Attribution tooltip integrated directly into the main newsroom title.
*Dedicated transparency panel describing project purpose, data sourcing, and newsroom principles.
*Attribution and infrastructure acknowledgement for:
	-https://api2.warera.io/trpc/
	-https://gateway.warerastats.io/trpc/
*Expanded transparency messaging emphasizing credibility, journalism, and responsible data usage.
*Enhanced newsroom branding and informational accessibility through contextual hover-based documentation.

###Improved

*Refined newsroom header presentation with integrated information access directly beside the News Desk title.
*Improved tooltip layering and rendering behavior to ensure visibility above panels, navigation elements, and scrolling containers.
*Enhanced tooltip readability through dedicated newsroom-styled presentation.
*Refined visual hierarchy of newsroom metadata and project attribution.

###Technical

*Implemented standalone newsroom information tooltip architecture.
*Improved z-index and overflow handling across header and navigation layers.
*Added reusable tooltip rendering patterns for future informational UI elements.
*Refined header component structure to better support future newsroom branding features.

###UX

*Users can now quickly understand the purpose, data sources, and operational principles of News Desk without leaving the application.
*Improved transparency regarding data collection practices and third-party integrations.
*Reduced ambiguity regarding the project's relationship with War Era services and statistics providers.


##[0.4.3-beta] - 2026-06-19

###Added

*Live Event Toast notification system for newly detected timeline events.
*Automatic toast suppression while the user is actively viewing the Timeline tab.
*Dedicated toast container integrated into the navigation bar area.
*Animated toast entrance and exit transitions using slide-up motion.
*Audio notification support for live event alerts.
*Market Intelligence live activity indicator.
*Animated signal-strength style status indicator to visually represent continuous real-time market monitoring.
*Persistent Price Index chart container within the Commodity Prices panel.
*Dedicated chart region separated from commodity list rendering.
*Market order dataset separation between commodity trading orders and equipment market transactions.
*Automatic market view rotation architecture for alternating market datasets.
*Support for equipment transaction parsing from itemMarket transaction history.
*Support for equipment item code normalization and human-readable equipment naming.

###Improved

*Live timeline monitoring now generates contextual toast notifications using generated event titles rather than relying on raw API payload fields.
*Improved event title handling by reusing the existing buildTitle() intelligence generation pipeline.
*Enhanced visibility of newly detected events when browsing non-timeline sections.
*Improved market monitoring UX through persistent visual feedback indicating live updates.
*Improved Commodity Prices panel layout by allowing commodity lists to scroll independently from chart visualizations.
*Refined chart placement to behave similarly to frozen spreadsheet rows, ensuring trend visibility at all times.
*Improved market intelligence readability through separation of data lists and trend visualizations.
*Enhanced support for equipment market activity alongside traditional commodity order books.
*Improved handling of mixed market datasets without requiring changes to existing rendering and reporting systems.
*Refined toast notification styling and positioning within the navigation area.
*Improved handling of long event headlines within constrained toast layouts.

###Technical

*Introduced dedicated live-event toast rendering pipeline.
*Added conditional notification logic based on active tab state.
*Implemented reusable event title generation through integration with buildTitle().
*Added toast animation lifecycle management including timed appearance and removal states.
*Added market live-indicator animation framework using CSS keyframe sequences.
*Separated commodity and equipment order collection pipelines for future market expansion.
*Prepared rotating market data architecture allowing alternating dataset presentation without modifying downstream rendering logic.
*Added support for extracting equipment transaction pricing from itemMarket transaction payloads.
*Introduced dedicated chart container architecture for persistent market visualizations.
*Refactored market panel rendering structure to support independently scrolling content regions.
*Expanded market intelligence framework to accommodate future multi-category market analytics.

###UX

*Users now receive unobtrusive live notifications when important events occur while reading Battles, Market, or Jobs pages.
*Price Index trend visualization remains visible while browsing large commodity datasets.
*Market Intelligence section now more clearly communicates that data is continuously updated in real time.
*Reduced risk of missing important geopolitical or military developments while navigating away from the Timeline page.


